The paper deals with a geometric optimization problem of finding k disks with centers on a line that cover a given set of points in the plane. This problem involves computational geometry (cs.CG) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) to efficiently solve it. The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which are often studied in the subfield of approximation algorithms and heuristics (cs.DM). The problem involves optimizing a certain objective function subject to constraints, which is a common theme in game theory (cs.GT) and optimization (cs.SI).
